Hey yall, I have been trying to use the 2024 release of wpi lib and game tools and my falcons don’t work. My rio is running 2024_v2.1 and has the v6.0.0f1 firmware. I have tried with every single 2024 phoenix 6 version for the falcons as well as the 22.2.0.0 v5 firmware. Whenever I run the code normally or run it in test mode, the falcon’s led indicator flash orange as if it was disabled. If i try to run them in code or manually run them via tuner x nothing happens. Please help. (My robot works on the 2023 version with firmware 22.1.1.0. Idk if that will help)

Note that CTRE has not yet released their first non-beta 2024 release (they needed to wait for WPILib to do our kickoff release).

[CTRE] 2024 Kickoff Software! …almost Programming
It’s that time of year again! We at CTRE can’t wait for Kickoff and are just as eager as y’all for the initial season release of software. Thanks to a whole lot of testers and an awesome off-season of development (more on that later…) we’re more excited than ever to see how teams use Phoenix to create amazing robots and push the boundaries of software development in FRC.
